 <text>
  <front>
   <head>Elegie - (C, Pr.)</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1">
     <l n="1">Mos fuit antiquis, sacrorum maxime princeps,</l>
     <l n="2">Barbara cum Romae nupta puella foret,</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2">
     <l n="3">Hanc primum ad sacrae Iunonis ducere templa,</l>
     <l n="4">Unguibus atque comis tonsis abire simul,</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3">
     <l n="5">Ut quos barbaricos mores vel ritus haberet</l>
     <l n="6">Linqueret et Romae crederet esse satam.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="4">
     <l n="7">Ergo, si qua meis cernes lasciva libellis</l>
     <l n="8">Nec satis a sacro principe digna legi,</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="5">
     <l n="9">Tonde quod incultum est, quod nostrae turpe Thaliae:</l>
     <l n="10">Utere Romani tu quoque more ducis.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="6">
     <l n="11">Sin aliquid dignum vel quid rude carmen habebit,</l>
     <l n="12">Error erit noster, gloria tota tua.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
